<protolog id="rid.6845_nm.5502" type="description" xmlns="http://namesforlife.com/ns/protolog" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://namesforlife.com/ns/protolog file:/C:/NamesforLife/workspace/namesforlife-schema/protolog.xsd"><organism doi="10.1601/nm.5502" rank="genus">Allofustis</organism><reference id="rid.6845"><citation citation-type="journal"><authors><person-name><surname>Collins</surname><given-names>M.D.</given-names></person-name><person-name><surname>Higgins</surname><given-names>R.</given-names></person-name><person-name><surname>Messier</surname><given-names>S.</given-names></person-name><person-name><surname>Fortin</surname><given-names>M.</given-names></person-name><person-name><surname>Hutson</surname><given-names>R.A.</given-names></person-name><person-name><surname>Lawson</surname><given-names>P.A.</given-names></person-name><person-name><surname>Falsen</surname><given-names>E.</given-names></person-name></authors><article-title>Allofustis seminis gen. nov., sp. nov., a novel Gram-positive, catalase-negative, rod-shaped bacterium from pig semen</article-title><year>2003</year><volume>53</volume><issue>3</issue><fpage>811</fpage><lpage>814</lpage><source id="117">International Journal of Systematic and Evolutionary Microbiology</source><abbrev>Int J Syst Evol Microbiol</abbrev><issn>1466-5026</issn><essn>1466-5034</essn><pub-id pub-id-type="doi">10.1099/ijs.0.02484-0</pub-id><pub-id pub-id-type="pmid">12807205</pub-id></citation></reference><content><p class="title"><s>Description of <em>Allofustis</em> gen. nov.</s></p><p class="etymology"><s><em>Allofustis</em> (Al.lo.fus′tis. Gr. prefix <em>allo</em> the other; L. masc. n. <em>fustis</em> stick; N.L. masc. n. <em>Allofustis</em> the other stick or rod).</s></p><p class="description"><s>Cells are Gram-positive, non-spore-forming rods.</s><s>Facultatively anaerobic and catalase-negative.</s><s>Arginine dihydrolase, leucine arylamidase and pyroglutamic acid arylamidase are produced.</s><s>Indole-negative.</s><s>Nitrate is not reduced.</s><s>Voges–Proskauer-negative.</s><s>The long-chain cellular fatty acids are of the straight-chain saturated and monounsaturated types.</s><s>Cell wall murein is based on l-lys variation a1<em>α</em> (type l-Lys-direct).</s><s>The type species is <em>Allofustis seminis</em>.</s><s>The G+C content of genomic DNA of the type species is 39 mol%.</s></p></content></protolog>